summary: All these new Michael Sheen stans, they don’t know what it was like. They don’t understand going to see a midnight showing of...
body:
All these new Michael Sheen stans, they don’t know what it was like. They don’t understand going to see a midnight showing of Twilight 2 not because you actually enjoyed Twilight but because you knew Michael Sheen was going to be campy as hell in it and you were 100% right. “Why did he laugh like that? That was so weird!” Your friends would all say. because ACTING you’d know deep down in your heart.


Or sitting through fucking TRON because you knew Michael Sheen was going to be campy as hell and BEING 100% RIGHT.

Or going to see FAR FROM THE MADDING CROWD and telling everyone that Michael Sheen was your future husband, only to watch him NOT be cool and campy and instead be gross as hell, and have your BEST FRIEND lean over and be like “future husband, huh?” and both crack up so hard you think you’ll pass out.

Or having this poster from the Damned United take up so much room on your wall that your boyfriend gets a weird complex about it.
